      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2113: The retry state is never reset when a new registration/connectivity cycle starts after retries are exhausted. Once `exhausted` is set, later identity announcement failures return immediately for the lifetime of the account unless a success callback happens first, which can leave presence tracking broken after a subsequent GSM standby/reconnect. Reset the retry state when starting a fresh DHT/registration cycle, or before scheduling retries for a new identity announcement cycle.\n```suggestion\n// When starting a fresh registration/DHT cycle:\nif (identityRetryState_) {\n    identityRetryState_-\u003etimer.cancel();\n    identityRetryState_.reset();\n}\n```",
