      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2131: `asio::steady_timer` is modified directly from `identityAnnouncedCb`, which may be invoked from the DHT/account manager thread rather than the manager io_context thread. Asio timer objects are not safe for concurrent unsynchronized access, and this can race with the async wait handler or cancellation during shutdown. Marshal all timer operations onto the timer\u0027s executor/io_context, or protect the retry state with the same serialization mechanism used elsewhere in this class.\n```suggestion\nauto weakThis \u003d weak();\nasio::post(*Manager::instance().ioContext(), [weakThis, delaySec] {\n    if (auto account \u003d weakThis.lock()) {\n        auto\u0026 state \u003d *account-\u003eidentityRetryState_;\n        state.timer.cancel();\n        state.timer.expires_after(std::chrono::seconds(delaySec));\n        state.timer.async_wait(/* existing handler */);\n    }\n});\n```",
